  "text": "An ontology such as WordNet could be used to find parent concepts shared between labels to apply a more general annotation, as was done in [CITATION_1] . For example, instead of the top-middle image in Figure 6 being labelled \"bird tree insect lizard,\" when it is clearly a leopard, the common parent between \"lizard,\" \"bird,\" and \"insect\", which is \"animal,\" could be used. This would more naturally model the concepts we have chosen.",
